' ========== FLOW ==========
start

' ---- Core Foundations ----
fork
:Arrays & Strings;
note right: Foundation for Prefix Sum,\nSliding Window, Two Pointers
fork again
:Linked Lists;
note right: In-place traversal,\nFast & Slow Pointers
fork again
:Stacks & Queues;
note right: Monotonic Stack,\nBacktracking, BFS
end fork

' ---- Intermediate ----
fork
:Heaps (Priority Queues);
note right: Top K Elements,\nMerging Intervals
fork again
:HashMaps / HashSets;
note right: Used for Prefix Sum,\nSliding Window, and DP (Memoization)
fork again
:Sorting Algorithms;
note right: Essential for Intervals,\nBinary Search, and Optimization
end fork

' ---- Hierarchical Structures ----
fork
:Trees & BSTs;
note right: DFS, Modified Binary Search,\nRecursion Practice
fork again
:Graphs;
note right: BFS, DFS,\nShortest Path Problems
fork again
:2D Arrays / Matrices;
note right: Matrix Traversal,\nIsland & Pathfinding Problems
end fork

' ---- Advanced Patterns ----
:Recursion & Backtracking;
note right: Foundation for DFS,\nCombinations, Permutations

:Dynamic Programming;
note right: Builds on Recursion,\nOverlapping Subproblems and Memoization

:Algorithmic Pattern Integration;
note right: Combine all concepts to\nsolve complex problems efficiently

stop
